title: Barbeque Chicken Roll Ups (in the Crock Pot)
directions: Spray Crock Pot with non-stick spray
In a large bowl combine chili sauce, brown sugar, honey, vinegar, red pepper flakes, red pepper, garlic and onion. Mix completely and pour over chicken.
Turn Crock Pot on low for at least 4 hours.
After 4 (could be more) hours use 2 forks and shred chicken let cook on low for another 1/2 hour or more.
Spread chicken onto Mission Tortilla. Sprinkle some grated cheese (I used sharp cheddar) over chicken. Make a line of jalapenos and roll up to ensure that you get a jalapeno in every bite.
ingredients: 1/4 C vinegar (any kind will be fine)
